main event: A witness in Hollywood Hills, California observed a strange object crossing the sky at a high speed on August 9, 1965.
interesting points: The object appeared to be moving at a tremendous speed and did not disappear like a falling star.
The witness observed the object through binoculars and a telescope for around 2 minutes.
The object did not behave like a satellite, as it could be directed at will.
There were many airplanes in the sky that night, but the witness was certain this was not an airplane.
The witness had previously been a skeptic about UFOs, but felt this sighting could not be explained.
sighted object: a strange, fast-moving object in the sky
witnesses: the witness, his wife, son, stepson, and a friend
